The paper deals with response selection in retrieval-based chatbots, which is a subfield of natural language processing (NLP) and conversational AI. Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves information retrieval (IR) techniques for selecting the best response, which makes cs.IR a likely sub-category as well. The proposed model TripleNet uses attention mechanisms and deep learning techniques, which are common in the sub-categories cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Finally, the paper also discusses the performance of the proposed model on large-scale datasets, which could fall under the sub-category cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
